  "body": "The code:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n  function _burn(address account, uint256 value) internal {\r\n    require(account != 0);\r\n    require(value <= _balances[account]);\r\n\r\n    _totalSupply = _totalSupply.sub(value);\r\n    _balances[account] = _balances[account].sub(value);\r\n    emit Transfer(account, address(0), value);\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\nFrom:\r\n\r\n> https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/blob/master/contracts/token/ERC20/ERC20.sol#L186-L193\r\n\r\nHas an unnecessary `require(value <= _balances[account]);` This test is already performed as part of the following line `_balances[account] = _balances[account].sub(value);`.\r\n\r\nLikewise for `burnFrom`.",
